1
00:00:17,266 --> 00:00:18,266
Zein

2
00:00:19,727 --> 00:00:22,229
you're the only one who can save Supremo

3
00:00:22,445 --> 00:00:24,572
and this university.

4
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,234
We can do this.

5
00:00:28,277 --> 00:00:29,362
Don't give up.

6
00:00:30,946 --> 00:00:33,449
I hope after this night ends

7
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:36,160
you can still forgive me.

8
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,913
Do you want me to repeat myself?

9
00:00:42,613 --> 00:00:45,866
I can't take this pain anymore, Ace.

10
00:00:46,003 --> 00:00:48,964
Did you ever love Ace Craige?

11
00:00:50,257 --> 00:00:51,257
No.

12
00:00:53,135 --> 00:00:54,470
Did you really love me?

13
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:00,726
Who could endure loving you?

14
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:03,979
I want you to fight.

15
00:01:05,981 --> 00:01:06,981
Not for me

16
00:01:09,151 --> 00:01:10,277
but for your friends.

17
00:01:10,903 --> 00:01:12,321
Most especially for yourself.

18
00:01:13,739 --> 00:01:15,324
No matter what happens

19
00:01:18,391 --> 00:01:19,434
you'll always be

20
00:01:20,823 --> 00:01:21,823
my queen.

21
00:01:22,653 --> 00:01:24,155
Liam Rivera is.

22
00:01:24,291 --> 00:01:25,710
Madam Violet's son?

23
00:01:26,502 --> 00:01:28,879
She wants Liam to be the Supremo.

24
00:01:30,438 --> 00:01:33,315
Don't you recognize this symbol?

25
00:01:34,848 --> 00:01:36,725
This is the symbol of Raze Silvenia.

26
00:01:52,778 --> 00:01:53,904
I want you to fight.

27
00:01:57,311 --> 00:01:58,311
Not for me

28
00:02:00,327 --> 00:02:01,746
but for your friends

29
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,540
and especially yourself.

30
00:02:08,208 --> 00:02:09,208
Don't worry.

31
00:02:12,196 --> 00:02:13,281
I'm still breathing

32
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,843
and a promise is a promise.

33
00:02:25,936 --> 00:02:26,936
Hoy...

34
00:02:32,276 --> 00:02:33,276
Hoy.

35
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:38,616
Hoy.

36
00:03:49,839 --> 00:03:51,090
What do you want?

37
00:03:52,731 --> 00:03:54,441
Why did you turn your back on him?

38
00:03:56,527 --> 00:03:58,070
Why didn't you fight for him?

39
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:00,740
Darling?

40
00:04:02,366 --> 00:04:03,742
Don't call me that!

41
00:04:06,912 --> 00:04:08,137
Let go.

42
00:04:08,956 --> 00:04:09,957
I said let go!

43
00:04:14,253 --> 00:04:15,253
Don't be afraid.

44
00:04:40,654 --> 00:04:41,654
Darling

45
00:04:44,074 --> 00:04:45,074
please come back.

46
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:47,555
Supremo asked me to send this message.

47
00:05:28,382 --> 00:05:29,382
Supremo...

48
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:14,558
Raze Silvenia

49
00:07:15,642 --> 00:07:16,894
who are you really?

50
00:07:18,437 --> 00:07:19,437
One!

51
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:24,025
Two!

52
00:07:30,949 --> 00:07:32,242
Three!

53
00:07:35,086 --> 00:07:36,086
Three!

54
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:21,625
Are you an ally

55
00:08:22,751 --> 00:08:23,752
or an enemy?

56
00:08:24,127 --> 00:08:25,920
Let his wound bleed.

57
00:08:26,181 --> 00:08:29,309
Clean it with warm water
until he's clean from the poison.

58
00:08:43,985 --> 00:08:45,212
Something got into Vanessa's eye.

59
00:08:45,237 --> 00:08:47,114
I was just helping her get it out.

60
00:08:48,377 --> 00:08:50,671
Your breath stinks! Stop it!

61
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,784
Whatever, guys.

62
00:08:53,906 --> 00:08:55,742
As if it's not obvious.

63
00:08:57,856 --> 00:08:58,774
So...

64
00:08:58,901 --> 00:09:00,235
where have you been?

65
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:02,786
It's almost Bloody Night!

66
00:09:08,547 --> 00:09:10,465
It doesn't matter.

67
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:14,344
Wow

68
00:09:14,369 --> 00:09:16,704
so that's how she is when she's in love.

69
00:09:17,931 --> 00:09:19,892
She's so different now.

70
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:21,393
Right, Je?

71
00:09:23,332 --> 00:09:24,875
You're right, my Vanessa.

72
00:09:25,386 --> 00:09:26,095
Hey!

73
00:09:26,244 --> 00:09:28,204
And when did I belong you?

74
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,568
Hmm...

75
00:09:29,651 --> 00:09:32,112
Yesterday, when you kissed me.

76
00:09:32,487 --> 00:09:33,447
Excuse me!

77
00:09:33,472 --> 00:09:35,016
I tripped! I didn't mean to do that!

78
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:35,803
Oh my god.

79
00:09:35,828 --> 00:09:37,162
Wow.

80
00:09:37,508 --> 00:09:39,301
She tripped

81
00:09:39,326 --> 00:09:41,203
right on my lips.

82
00:09:42,998 --> 00:09:43,998
Right?

83
00:09:45,992 --> 00:09:47,352
Why did you turn your back on him?

84
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:48,876
Why didn't you fight for him

85
00:09:49,087 --> 00:09:50,087
darling?

86
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:53,091
Don't call me that!

87
00:09:54,426 --> 00:09:55,677
I'm sorry, Ace.

88
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:57,596
I can't come back to you.

89
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:01,141
Let's just let fate decide what happens.

90
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,810
There's still a lot that can happen.

91
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:06,939
I refuse to be your weakness.

92
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:12,765
During wartime

93
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:17,218
it was common for wives,
fiancées, and girlfriends

94
00:11:17,384 --> 00:11:20,327
to be kept waiting for years on end.

95
00:11:20,897 --> 00:11:26,111
The lucky ones carried on
correspondence through letters.

96
00:11:26,184 --> 00:11:28,144
Most of the women

97
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:32,107
held onto those letters
from their loved ones.

98
00:11:32,899 --> 00:11:34,151
Just think about it.

99
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:36,278
Some letters arrive late.

100
00:11:36,528 --> 00:11:40,574
Some don't even make it
on time to hold meaning.

101
00:11:40,949 --> 00:11:44,536
And sadly, some never arrive at all.

102
00:11:45,242 --> 00:11:46,242
For what?

103
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,055
People continued to write.

104
00:11:48,263 --> 00:11:49,557
- They wrote about ordinary
- You know...

105
00:11:49,582 --> 00:11:52,603
things like what
they ate that day.

106
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:54,421
The most mundane things.

107
00:11:54,796 --> 00:11:59,176
Because during war, ordinary
life becomes something precious.

108
00:12:07,976 --> 00:12:12,189
Loving each other briefly was enough.

109
00:12:12,947 --> 00:12:14,490
No, it's not.

110
00:12:15,650 --> 00:12:16,943
I want to love you

111
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:18,445
openly.

112
00:12:20,308 --> 00:12:21,308
Darling

113
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:23,460
why can't you trust me?

114
00:12:25,386 --> 00:12:26,929
I trust you, Ace

115
00:12:27,772 --> 00:12:29,565
with my whole life.

116
00:12:34,127 --> 00:12:35,504
I'm giving up.

117
00:12:35,962 --> 00:12:38,590
I just can't fight for this shit anymore.

118
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,051
We haven't even started yet

119
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:43,242
and you're ending it just like that?

120
00:12:46,736 --> 00:12:47,736
Darling...

121
00:12:47,982 --> 00:12:49,483
Stop calling me that.

122
00:12:56,097 --> 00:12:57,097
Zein

123
00:12:58,636 --> 00:13:00,263
I'll give you another chance.

124
00:13:01,693 --> 00:13:04,334
If you walk ten steps away from me

125
00:13:06,175 --> 00:13:07,801
and you don't look back,

126
00:13:09,451 --> 00:13:11,452
forget everything between us.

127
00:13:18,124 --> 00:13:19,124
Here

128
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:20,549
these are your new clothes.

129
00:13:21,348 --> 00:13:22,348
Wear it

130
00:13:22,373 --> 00:13:23,958
and I'll show you our office.

131
00:13:26,839 --> 00:13:29,091
And where do you think you're going?

132
00:13:31,226 --> 00:13:32,561
To the restroom

133
00:13:32,586 --> 00:13:33,586
to change.

134
00:13:34,221 --> 00:13:35,221
No.

135
00:13:36,288 --> 00:13:37,288
Change here.

136
00:13:38,123 --> 00:13:39,333
In front of you?

137
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:40,693
Why?

138
00:13:41,695 --> 00:13:42,863
Do you want to?

139
00:13:44,656 --> 00:13:46,158
In your dreams.

140
00:13:57,745 --> 00:13:59,038
You still lack training.

141
00:14:00,044 --> 00:14:01,253
Just so you know

142
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:04,194
those aren't just the moves I know.

143
00:14:14,057 --> 00:14:15,850
Maybe you'd like to move your hand off me?

144
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,728
I told you

145
00:14:22,665 --> 00:14:24,000
you can look at me

146
00:14:24,993 --> 00:14:26,661
but you're not allowed to touch me.

147
00:14:33,879 --> 00:14:38,509
I'm ready to fight even death for you.

148
00:14:50,388 --> 00:14:51,472
This tastes disgusting.

149
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:52,678
Don't spit it out!

150
00:14:56,144 --> 00:14:57,144
Supremo?

151
00:14:59,848 --> 00:15:01,272
Whatever you choose

152
00:15:04,402 --> 00:15:05,779
as long as it makes you happy.

153
00:15:07,864 --> 00:15:09,491
Whatever your decision is

154
00:15:11,910 --> 00:15:13,161
don't be afraid.

155
00:15:15,111 --> 00:15:16,111
I think

156
00:15:17,892 --> 00:15:19,644
this is really goodbye for us.

157
00:15:24,177 --> 00:15:25,595
I love you.

158
00:15:26,299 --> 00:15:27,551
Zein.

159
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:45,193
♪ Oh darling. ♪

160
00:15:47,737 --> 00:15:53,743
♪ How beautiful it is to love you. ♪

161
00:15:55,704 --> 00:16:01,126
♪ I will lie beside you. ♪

162
00:16:03,628 --> 00:16:08,091
♪ I'll always be here for you. ♪

163
00:16:11,443 --> 00:16:12,444
♪ Darling... ♪

164
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,402
You're wasting your
energy by staring, Ms. Shion.

165
00:16:31,301 --> 00:16:32,886
He's still not here?

166
00:16:33,613 --> 00:16:35,865
I haven't seen him all day.

167
00:16:41,079 --> 00:16:43,764
Maybe he's not planning to come back.

168
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:46,754
No way.

169
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:49,590
Or maybe

170
00:16:50,216 --> 00:16:52,010
he's with someone else?

171
00:17:01,675 --> 00:17:02,675
Kidding

172
00:17:03,195 --> 00:17:04,321
of course.

173
00:17:05,822 --> 00:17:07,407
Be patient, Ms. Shion.

174
00:17:07,859 --> 00:17:09,152
He'll return.

175
00:17:11,446 --> 00:17:13,573
I just want this day to be over.

176
00:17:15,107 --> 00:17:16,107
Same.

177
00:17:16,578 --> 00:17:17,621
All of us feel that way.

178
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:08,963
I know what's bothering you.

179
00:18:11,270 --> 00:18:12,939
Fuck off, Nicky.

180
00:18:16,643 --> 00:18:18,269
I saw him.

181
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,184
He's with someone.

182
00:18:35,978 --> 00:18:37,340
I didn't ask.

183
00:18:39,876 --> 00:18:42,215
But that's not what
your eyes are telling me.

184
00:18:46,797 --> 00:18:48,507
You’re so fragile

185
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:51,067
and easy to break, Zein.

186
00:18:52,789 --> 00:18:54,793
Where’s that monster you’re hiding?

187
00:18:57,264 --> 00:18:58,574
Let it go, Zein.

188
00:18:59,829 --> 00:19:01,455
Protect yourself.

189
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:07,551
Thanks for the advice.

190
00:20:28,973 --> 00:20:30,039
Next.

191
00:20:53,449 --> 00:20:54,491
Next.

192
00:21:35,714 --> 00:21:36,757
Next.

193
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:49,608
Hi, Supremo.

194
00:22:05,229 --> 00:22:06,772
Thanks for last night.

195
00:22:07,916 --> 00:22:09,501
I really appreciate it.

196
00:22:13,035 --> 00:22:14,620
Anything for you, Supremo.

197
00:22:27,286 --> 00:22:30,789
Is it true that dogs can't look up?

198
00:22:31,538 --> 00:22:33,814
- Dave, stop it.
- Why?

199
00:22:33,893 --> 00:22:35,894
Have you seen a dog looking up?

200
00:22:35,991 --> 00:22:37,034
How about you, Van?

201
00:22:38,521 --> 00:22:41,274
Dave, don't involve me with your nonsense.

202
00:22:41,275 --> 00:22:45,013
What about my nonsense?

203
00:22:45,768 --> 00:22:48,020
Do you want to get punched?

204
00:22:51,911 --> 00:22:54,664
All classes are suspended.

205
00:22:55,348 --> 00:22:59,727
I repeat all classes are suspended.

206
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,714
A general meeting will be
held at the conference room.

207
00:23:03,089 --> 00:23:05,925
1:30 P.M. Mandatory.

208
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,915
I don't like this.

209
00:23:38,916 --> 00:23:40,793
I have a bad feeling.

210
00:23:42,153 --> 00:23:43,822
Whatever their plans is

211
00:23:44,379 --> 00:23:45,938
we stay together.

212
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:01,898
I swear I have no idea.

213
00:24:02,190 --> 00:24:03,470
Do you know anything about this?

214
00:24:04,317 --> 00:24:05,317
Promise

215
00:24:05,401 --> 00:24:06,611
I don't know.

216
00:24:25,572 --> 00:24:27,725
- What's happening here?
- How long will this take?

217
00:24:27,965 --> 00:24:28,965
I have no idea.

218
00:25:24,362 --> 00:25:26,572
Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen.

219
00:25:27,918 --> 00:25:30,253
Are you tired of this hellhole?

220
00:25:31,364 --> 00:25:32,490
Good news.

221
00:25:33,514 --> 00:25:36,655
Soon freedom will be within your grasp.

222
00:25:42,017 --> 00:25:43,517
Matt?

223
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,546
Are you okay?

224
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:47,186
Something's wrong here.

225
00:25:47,679 --> 00:25:49,882
Nazzer and Nicky aren't here.

226
00:25:52,077 --> 00:25:53,693
Any day now

227
00:25:54,022 --> 00:25:56,921
your suffering will end.

228
00:25:58,991 --> 00:26:01,159
From Philippine High University

229
00:26:01,644 --> 00:26:03,921
to Hell University.

230
00:26:06,209 --> 00:26:10,913
This place has been a witness
of your resiliency and strength.

231
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:15,817
But all things come to an end.

232
00:26:18,123 --> 00:26:20,569
Even if this story reaches its end

233
00:26:20,595 --> 00:26:21,960
it won't be forgotten.

234
00:26:22,657 --> 00:26:25,944
You will all remain
within this place's story.

235
00:26:33,462 --> 00:26:36,710
We have been experimenting
on a formula for years now.

236
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:41,530
A formula that can bring back the dead.

237
00:26:45,412 --> 00:26:46,829
What is this nonsense again?

238
00:26:46,854 --> 00:26:47,854
Are they joking?

239
00:27:00,082 --> 00:27:02,319
Now that we've almost completed it,

240
00:27:03,492 --> 00:27:07,991
I'm asking everyone to
cooperate one last time.

241
00:27:22,556 --> 00:27:23,516
What is this?

242
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:24,934
What's happening?

243
00:27:31,333 --> 00:27:32,543
Now

244
00:27:32,568 --> 00:27:34,405
all of you must rest.

245
00:28:51,311 --> 00:28:52,397
Supremo?

246
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:05,450
Darling

247
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,257
please come back.

248
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,120
I will.

249
00:29:57,992 --> 00:29:59,034
Zein?

250
00:29:59,515 --> 00:30:00,515
Zein.

251
00:30:01,382 --> 00:30:02,382
You're awake

252
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:03,550
Mia

253
00:30:04,228 --> 00:30:05,521
where are the others?

254
00:30:07,819 --> 00:30:09,348
Is it just us here?

255
00:30:10,731 --> 00:30:12,150
I don't know, Zein.

256
00:30:13,727 --> 00:30:14,895
I'm scared.

257
00:30:23,863 --> 00:30:24,863
Zein?

258
00:30:32,759 --> 00:30:33,759
That one.

259
00:30:34,094 --> 00:30:35,943
- Come here!
- What will you do with her?

260
00:30:40,463 --> 00:30:41,463
Stop!

261
00:30:53,392 --> 00:30:54,810
Let me go!

262
00:30:56,228 --> 00:30:57,897
Let me go!

263
00:31:03,139 --> 00:31:04,966
Help me!

264
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,320
Help!

265
00:31:08,161 --> 00:31:10,179
This is all my fault, Zein.

266
00:31:11,420 --> 00:31:12,546
Mia

267
00:31:13,329 --> 00:31:14,830
what are you saying?

268
00:31:15,956 --> 00:31:17,625
This isn't your fault.

269
00:31:18,481 --> 00:31:19,481
Even if you are

270
00:31:20,085 --> 00:31:21,587
all of us are at fault too.

271
00:31:22,556 --> 00:31:24,599
I made a huge mistake, Zein.

272
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:27,800
Mia

273
00:31:28,302 --> 00:31:29,302
whatever that mistake is

274
00:31:29,303 --> 00:31:30,866
I don't care about it.

275
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,032
What's important is

276
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:34,850
we all escape from here.

277
00:31:37,930 --> 00:31:38,968
Thank you, Zein.

278
00:31:41,161 --> 00:31:44,068
Your forgiveness is important to me

279
00:31:45,287 --> 00:31:47,539
because I don’t think I can forgive myself.

280
00:31:51,569 --> 00:31:52,796
Listen to me.

281
00:31:54,100 --> 00:31:56,102
You need to be strong.

282
00:32:01,634 --> 00:32:02,676
I lied.

283
00:32:05,609 --> 00:32:08,507
I didn't find the map that
led us here by chance.

284
00:32:13,430 --> 00:32:14,430
Guys!

285
00:32:14,455 --> 00:32:15,998
I think we're almost there.

286
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:18,937
Are you sure this is the right path?

287
00:32:19,353 --> 00:32:20,353
Wow.

288
00:32:20,437 --> 00:32:22,690
I never pegged you as a complainer, Zein.

289
00:32:22,856 --> 00:32:25,142
You've always liked these kinds of things.

290
00:32:25,167 --> 00:32:26,418
Because when I make the plans,

291
00:32:26,443 --> 00:32:29,738
